1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:00:04,120 --> 00:00:07,360
Two years have passed since the war between

3
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:12,960
Marine Headquarters, the Seven Warlords,
and the Whitebeard Pirates.

4
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:19,440
On the deserted island Luscaina,
northwest of the Isle of Women...

5
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:21,610
Luffy!

6
00:00:22,170 --> 00:00:24,610
Yeah! I'm coming!

7
00:00:27,140 --> 00:00:29,580
I can't believe it.

8
00:00:29,580 --> 00:00:31,780
It's been two years already.

9
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:08,850
Hey!

10
00:01:11,790 --> 00:01:14,790
Watch it. She's my friend.

11
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:26,100
Luffy, the ship is ready
to set sail whenever you are!

12
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,770
Okay, thanks!

13
00:01:29,670 --> 00:01:30,940
That's amazing.

14
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:33,310
He's the boss of the island now.

15
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:40,380
Thing is, we became friends,
so eating them went out the window.

16
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:43,290
They do look tasty though.

17
00:01:43,850 --> 00:01:45,760
It's okay, Luffy.

18
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:49,360
All your favorite foods are on the ship.

19
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:53,560
I think I'd be a good wife
since I'm thoughtful like that.

20
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,270
I'm not getting married,
but thank you for the food!

21
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:00,800
I can't help loving that harsh side of you!

22
00:02:01,610 --> 00:02:04,380
Rayleigh left six months ago.

23
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:07,340
He must be waiting to meet you on Sabaody.

24
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:11,180
He was done teaching me the basics
in the first year and a half.

25
00:02:11,180 --> 00:02:14,220
It's time I said goodbye
to you guys and the island.

26
00:02:17,860 --> 00:02:18,860
Alright...

27
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:22,130
Let's go!

28
00:04:28,690 --> 00:04:31,890
Did you know that
Marine Headquarters moved?

29
00:04:31,890 --> 00:04:34,290
What? It was?

30
00:04:34,290 --> 00:04:38,430
Yeah, they switched places
with the G-1 Branch,

31
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:41,000
sandwiching the Red Line on either side.

32
00:04:41,570 --> 00:04:45,200
That's how determined Sengoku's successor is.

33
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:51,010
After all, he set up their headquarters
in the sea with the Four Emperors.

34
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:55,510
But thanks to the switch,
their HQ has less sway here,

35
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:58,150
so there are more lawless areas on the island.

36
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:04,760
Hmm... No wonder it seems
rougher here than two years ago.

37
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,460
Hey, did you see this?!

38
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:08,490
Yeah, I was shocked, too.

39
00:05:08,490 --> 00:05:12,900
I can't believe the Straw Hats have resurfaced!

40
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:18,240
For real. Not a peep outta them for two years,
so we thought they had to be dead.

41
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:21,640
They're even recruiting!

42
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:28,280
Pirates who survived the first half
of the Grand Line keep showing up.

43
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:33,180
He's enlisting them to expand his crew
before running wild in the New World!

44
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:36,690
Sounds exciting! Maybe I should join too!

45
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:38,160
No way!

46
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:41,890
There are people with bounties
over 100 million on the island now.

47
00:05:41,890 --> 00:05:44,960
They definitely ain't taking you!

48
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,900
What?!

49
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:57,270
Hey, don't say that!
Can't you do anything about it?

50
00:05:57,270 --> 00:06:01,610
Tickets are sold out!
What else would you expect?!

51
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:05,850
We're talking about the superstar
Soul King Brook's world tour!

52
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:08,550
This island is the tour's final stop!

53
00:06:08,550 --> 00:06:11,660
The place is already packed!

54
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:18,160
Manager!

55
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:22,400
I'll put on a great show today!

56
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:25,840
Yes, that'd be nice!

57
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:30,070
Your TD has gone platinum,
selling over a million copies!

58
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:33,710
You certainly are the King of Soul Music!

59
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:36,380
Listen to the crowd!

60
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:45,290
Soul King! Soul King! Soul King! Soul King!

61
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:41,950
Manager...

62
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:45,290
before the concert...

63
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,030
I need to tell you something.

64
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,500
What is it?

65
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,270
Come on, baby!

66
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:01,200
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

67
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:03,510
We are...

68
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:05,880
– Bone!
– Bone!

69
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:06,740
Bone!

70
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:07,840
– Bone!
– Bone!

71
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,810
Bone!

72
00:07:08,810 --> 00:07:09,980
– Bone!
– Bone!

73
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:10,380
Bone!

74
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:10,980
– Bone!
– Bone!

75
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:11,350
Bone!

76
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:11,880
– Bone!
– Bone!

77
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:12,280
Bone! Bone! Bone!

78
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:12,750
Bone! Bone! Bone!

79
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,250
Bone! Bone! Bone!

80
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:15,790
Bone!

81
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:24,860
♪ Bone to be wild! ♪

82
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,470
I can't believe it...

83
00:07:28,770 --> 00:07:30,630
How selfish can he be?!

84
00:07:30,630 --> 00:07:33,100
Hey, give me a transponder snail!

85
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:37,010
I'm not gonna let you
get away with this, Brook!

86
00:07:37,010 --> 00:07:42,510
Let's make today the greatest anniversary!

87
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:57,330
Women! Real ones!

88
00:07:58,160 --> 00:08:00,400
Ah, there's no doubt!

89
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,930
There are actual ladies in front of me!

90
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:11,580
Here, on this island, are the real ladies
I've been dreaming of, night after night!

91
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:13,680
Viva Sabaody!

92
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,980
I need a lady!

93
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:18,420
Sanji-kins!

94
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:21,280
We'll leave you here.

95
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:24,590
I don't want to part,
but I'm sure we'll meet again!

96
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:30,990
I never want to see you again!
Thank you for the ride! Say "hi" to Ivan! Bye!

97
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:32,430
The man, Sanji,

98
00:08:32,430 --> 00:08:35,600
has just come back from hell!

99
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,900
You know what they say?

100
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:40,300
Boys can't help being mean to girls they like.

101
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,840
It's true. It happened to me.

102
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:46,240
I won't ever forget him!

103
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:50,780
Wait for me, Nami my sweet, Robin my love!

104
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:03,030
Huh? Did I hear wrong?

105
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:06,800
A 55-million-belly bounty?

106
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,030
Check the poster again!

107
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:13,770
It says, "No bounties under 70 million."

108
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:17,510
We ain't dealing with no captains worth less than that.

109
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,750
How'd you guys even get here in one piece?

110
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:24,310
Dammit!

111
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:26,420
Get lost, scum.

112
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:29,820
Don't you know I'm the son
of Dragon the Revolutionary?!

113
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:35,460
We don't need no deadweight!

114
00:09:35,460 --> 00:09:37,930
We're an exclusive pirate crew!

115
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:40,130
We're in another league.

116
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:43,600
Don't think just anyone can join us.

117
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:46,200
Get lost.

118
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:54,240
Straw Hat Luffy is merciless.

119
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,680
Well yeah, he's already achieved so much.

120
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:02,090
Hey, Franky, how many people we got so far?

121
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:04,750
A hundred or so.

122
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:07,620
Three whole pirate crews have joined up.

123
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:09,760
Ten of them have bounties.

124
00:10:10,930 --> 00:10:15,570
That's good. And two of those
are high-profile rookies.

125
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:20,670
Wet-Haired Caribou
and Blood Spatter Coribou.

126
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:22,540
Both are known for killing Marines.

127
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:26,740
These brothers are captains with bounties
of 210 million and 190 million.

128
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,580
We'll get some use out of 'em!

129
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:34,620
Let's get more followers!
Old man, we need another round!

130
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:36,620
Y-Yes!

131
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:38,520
Hurry up!

132
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:43,090
Oh? You've been there
for a hot minute, babe.

133
00:10:43,530 --> 00:10:46,830
Stop drinking all alone and come join us!

134
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:49,270
She's a beauty.

135
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,870
Not on your life.

136
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:54,770
What?

137
00:10:55,370 --> 00:10:56,510
She turned him down...!

138
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:59,610
Hey, hey! You have to say yes!

139
00:10:59,610 --> 00:11:01,910
He's Straw Hat Luffy!

140
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:06,820
Remember? He's the crazy pirate who
burst into the Summit War two years ago!

141
00:11:06,820 --> 00:11:08,290
Ring any bells?

142
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:11,320
Waiting for a guy?

143
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:16,590
Gotta be some wimp who'd wail and beg
for mercy after hearing Captain Luffy's name!

144
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:18,500
Get over here already!

145
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,760
I'll only say it once!

146
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:25,700
I'm way out of your league, so there's
no way I'm drinking with you.

147
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,300
What?

148
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:32,510
Do you understand, Straw Hat... who?

149
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:35,180
I'm freakin' Straw Hat Luffy!

150
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:40,380
Hey, you'd better apologize! You're in danger!

151
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:41,120
Huh?

152
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:44,190
You've got a lot of nerve!

153
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,860
I'll handle her.

154
00:11:49,830 --> 00:11:52,400
So let me spell it out for you.

155
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,170
Either you have a drink with Captain Luffy...

156
00:11:55,170 --> 00:11:57,130
or you drink from this barrel.

157
00:11:57,130 --> 00:11:59,340
For your information, I have a bounty too.

158
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:02,240
I'm Cat Burglar Nami!

159
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,540
Don't mess with me!

160
00:12:04,310 --> 00:12:06,210
Lethal Green Star:

161
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,050
Devil!

162
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,420
Huh?

163
00:12:14,420 --> 00:12:16,050
Wh-What is this?!

164
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:19,190
The hell is this?

165
00:12:20,490 --> 00:12:22,430
Help me, Captain!

166
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:24,430
Get away from me, you dumbass!

167
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:28,430
What is that plant?

168
00:12:28,430 --> 00:12:31,570
Say, young lady, do you
wanna drink with me?

169
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,910
Usopp, long time no see!

170
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:44,450
I can't believe it! Look how strong you got!

171
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:48,920
You've blossomed a bunch yourself!

172
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:53,420
What?! She was waiting for that punk?!

173
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:55,630
Your handiwork?

174
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:58,190
Indeed! That's my new weapon: pop green!

175
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:02,870
It's not like I've been gazing at the sea,
doing nothing for two years.

176
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:04,470
I'm sorry, but...

177
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:08,610
I no longer belong to the Weak Trio
with you and Chopper.

178
00:13:08,610 --> 00:13:12,440
I became a warrior
who isn't fazed by anything!

179
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:16,310
Hey, dude! Did you do this to us?

180
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:19,480
What?! Sogeking?! Why?!

181
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,320
Usopp, forget about them!

182
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,720
Let's go somewhere else.

183
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:24,150
Plus, I need a favor.

184
00:13:24,150 --> 00:13:25,360
Wait, you assholes!

185
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,460
Huh, Luffy?!

186
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:27,620
We're going!

187
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:29,590
Hey, ma'am, you haven't paid yet!

188
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:42,840
Shit! They made us look bad!

189
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,740
Go get 'em!

190
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,540
Dammit!

191
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:51,610
Huh?! What are these black bubbles?!

192
00:13:55,690 --> 00:13:58,890
What the hell? A cloud?!

193
00:14:08,970 --> 00:14:10,970
Wh-What happened?!

194
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:14,600
And then I got to study up on some new tech.

195
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:17,140
Really? You were in the sky?

196
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:48,510
Find those two and kill them!

197
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:53,910
I have a report! At the Sabaody Archipelago...

198
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:57,210
What? The Straw Hats?!

199
00:14:57,210 --> 00:15:01,550
Yes, sir! It seems they're
recruiting new crew members there.

200
00:15:02,990 --> 00:15:04,990
Report this to HQ.

201
00:15:04,990 --> 00:15:07,190
This is bad if he's alive.

202
00:15:07,790 --> 00:15:09,630
Gather the troops on the double!

203
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:13,630
And intensify the search
on Sabaody Archipelago!

204
00:15:33,950 --> 00:15:35,390
Did I shake them?

205
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,760
Brook's holding a concert?

206
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:43,290
The Straw Hats are recruiting?

207
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:47,260
Just what is going on?

208
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,030
"Soul King"?

209
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:54,700
Wh-What?!

210
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:57,540
That swordsmoron was the first one here?!

211
00:15:57,540 --> 00:15:59,480
I can't believe it!

212
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,780
Our next voyage will be rough.

213
00:16:01,780 --> 00:16:07,520
Franky came second, about ten days ago,
and immediately went to see the ship.

214
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,520
The Sunny is safe, right?

215
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:14,160
Of course. Not a scratch on her,
and the coating's already done.

216
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:15,490
That's good.

217
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:17,730
He did a good job.

218
00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:20,560
There's no regret for honorable wounds!

219
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:23,730
– Yes! A year to heal!
– Yes! A year to heal!

220
00:16:23,730 --> 00:16:26,640
I didn't know you had such
a strong sense of duty.

221
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:29,570
Thank you, Duval.

222
00:16:29,570 --> 00:16:31,710
What, you think I'm handsome?

223
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:34,840
I returned the favor, Young Master.

224
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,850
Whether it was raining or windy,

225
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:40,050
dangerous pirates were after your ship.

226
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:43,520
But I fought day after day
with cuts and bruises!

227
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:45,860
Those were painful times!

228
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:48,120
– Boss Duval!
– Boss Duval!

229
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,360
Even so, how did you get hurt so badly?

230
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:55,060
Well, fall for me... I mean,
listen to me, Young Master.

231
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:58,300
That's because the Marines finally...

232
00:16:55,730 --> 00:16:58,300
And Nami was the third...

233
00:16:58,300 --> 00:17:01,500
Nami my sweet!

234
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,510
Where is she?!

235
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:06,110
She went out shopping to kill time.

236
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,080
What about my story?!

237
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:11,750
♪ Nami's shopping! Nami's shopping! ♪

238
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:15,690
Usopp arrived fourth a few
days ago and went to town.

239
00:17:15,690 --> 00:17:18,560
Chopper arrived fifth yesterday.

240
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:21,930
Brook came here today for a concert.

241
00:17:21,930 --> 00:17:22,730
A concert?

242
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,730
And then you came.

243
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:31,940
So seven members including you have
already arrived on the archipelago.

244
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:35,410
We haven't seen Nico Robin or Luffy yet.

245
00:17:35,410 --> 00:17:39,540
It's extremely difficult just
to get to this island.

246
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,910
You all are quite impressive.

247
00:17:41,910 --> 00:17:44,750
It's nice you'll be able to reunite.

248
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:49,850
Yeah. That aside, I can't believe
you trained Luffy.

249
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:52,520
He must be incredibly strong now.

250
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:54,920
I haven't seen him in six months.

251
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:57,230
I'm excited to see his progress.

252
00:17:57,230 --> 00:18:00,060
Progress...

253
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:04,230
I wonder what kind of
"progress" Nami has made!

254
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:06,170
Hey, are you alright?

255
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:14,480
Hey, Zoro! Sanji! Robin!

256
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:17,380
We're finally back together, but you're acting weird!

257
00:18:18,310 --> 00:18:22,090
Zoro and Sanji, you guys have grown
so close over the past two years.

258
00:18:22,090 --> 00:18:25,490
But why aren't you talking to me?

259
00:18:25,860 --> 00:18:27,590
Hey, it's still following us.

260
00:18:27,890 --> 00:18:30,790
Oh, you're just being shy, you jerks!

261
00:18:30,790 --> 00:18:36,000
That tanuki knows a bit too much about us.

262
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,570
I've been thinking about that too...

263
00:18:38,570 --> 00:18:42,010
Could it be? Look at this.

264
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:44,110
There's no way...!

265
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:51,180
The real Cotton Candy Lover Chopper,
with a fifty-belly bounty!

266
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:52,250
It's their pet!

267
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:55,550
You guys changed a little, but I don't mind.

268
00:18:56,290 --> 00:19:00,790
They must've dumped it on the island
before they died, and now it's a stray.

269
00:19:01,220 --> 00:19:05,660
So it's following us because
it thinks its masters are back.

270
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,200
Then let's ditch that fox
and take this one instead.

271
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:12,640
If the pet is identical to the poster,
we'll look more authentic.

272
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:14,440
We're gonna keep it? What does it eat?

273
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:15,940
Cotton candy!

274
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:17,170
Don't got any!

275
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:21,640
We don't need you anymore! Go away!

276
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:26,920
Come here, Chopper.

277
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:30,950
Have a cucumber.

278
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:33,160
Scary! Robin's scary!

279
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:34,060
Now's our chance!

280
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:38,660
Oh, Robin!

281
00:19:38,660 --> 00:19:40,860
What? Hey, Nico Robin!

282
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:41,900
Who are they?

283
00:19:42,370 --> 00:19:44,400
This is really bad! Robin was abducted!

284
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,570
They're kidnappers!

285
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:51,310
Hey, shouldn't we report this to Captain Luffy?

286
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:53,980
What?! Have you guys seen Luffy already?

287
00:19:53,980 --> 00:19:54,980
You're right!

288
00:19:54,980 --> 00:19:56,450
They must have new members by now too!

289
00:19:57,180 --> 00:20:00,050
Yeah, we'd better rescue Robin already, huh?

290
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:01,350
Lead the way!

291
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:07,960
This is Sabaody! We caught Nico Robin!

292
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:11,230
With what looks like... a fox?
And it won't let go of her.

293
00:20:12,630 --> 00:20:16,230
I'd better hurry up.
They might all be here by now.

294
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:22,770
Hey, did you get hit?! The hell!

295
00:20:23,210 --> 00:20:24,640
What's with this guy?!

296
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,610
He shot her out of the blue!

297
00:20:26,610 --> 00:20:27,680
That's terrible!

298
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:30,050
Hey, stay with me!

299
00:20:30,610 --> 00:20:32,250
Why did you shoot?!

300
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,350
Did we do something to you?!

301
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:36,890
I said, "sorry," didn't I?!

302
00:20:36,890 --> 00:20:38,860
I mistook her for someone else!

303
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:43,290
Sorry. I was looking for
a couple that look just like you.

304
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:46,860
A long-haired woman and a long-nosed man.

305
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:49,970
You mistook her and shot her on the spot?!

306
00:20:49,970 --> 00:20:53,240
That Straw Hat Luffy is one nasty guy.

307
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:57,010
Huh? Don't tell me that you
got a problem with me?!

308
00:20:59,710 --> 00:21:00,840
Looks like you do.

309
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:08,180
Don't blame me! It's their fault!

310
00:21:09,290 --> 00:21:11,420
Hey, hang in there! You still with us?

311
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:14,860
Find those two already!

312
00:21:16,890 --> 00:21:19,300
We can't just let them get away!

313
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,200
Kill 'em and set an example!

314
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:42,120
Oh, did I bump you? Sorry!

315
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,550
Bye!

316
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:45,820
What's wrong with him?

317
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:48,360
Doesn't he know who Straw Hat Luffy is?

318
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:51,360
H-He's a dead man walking!

319
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:55,360
Wait just a minute!

320
00:22:03,110 --> 00:22:03,910
Huh?

321
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:08,440
That's Sabaody Archipelago in the distance.

322
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:13,250
Luffy, we have to say goodbye here.

323
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:16,490
We can't let them find out
about our relationship.

324
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:17,550
Uh-huh.

325
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:18,750
Put this on...

326
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,620
like this!

327
00:22:21,620 --> 00:22:24,060
I don't need that! It's too much!

328
00:22:24,060 --> 00:22:25,230
Is that so?

329
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,830
But in case something happens...

330
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,930
Uh-huh.

331
00:22:29,670 --> 00:22:31,370
You have to be careful.

332
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:34,240
Make sure you hide your face.

333
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:38,980
The world thinks you're dead, but...

334
00:22:39,310 --> 00:22:42,880
people still know what
you look like from two years ago.

335
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:46,280
If you cause trouble,
you won't be able to set sail.

336
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:48,020
I got it.

337
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:52,890
And in the backpack, I put 500
changes of clothes, 1,000 lunches,

338
00:22:52,890 --> 00:22:55,860
handkerchiefs and tissues,
5 years' worth of towels,

339
00:22:55,860 --> 00:23:01,200
3 years' worth of water and snacks,
silverware, toothbrushes, soap,

340
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:04,270
hand creams, three years' worth
of bug bite ointment, and...

341
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:06,170
That's way too much!

342
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:06,900
Oh?

343
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:11,440
I wish you a safe reunion with your crew.

344
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:14,510
Yeah. Thank you for everything!

345
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:17,180
Good luck!

346
00:23:17,180 --> 00:23:21,720
I heard that Sabaody has
become perilous these days.

347
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:27,460
Yes. That's why the Marines are paying
a lot of attention to what goes on there.

348
00:23:27,460 --> 00:23:29,590
Take extra care!

349
00:23:29,590 --> 00:23:30,330
Will do.

350
00:23:30,890 --> 00:23:36,900
If you need us, the Kuja Pirates
will always come to help you!

351
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:39,070
Please keep that in mind.

352
00:23:40,940 --> 00:23:43,710
And could you do me a favor?

353
00:23:43,710 --> 00:23:46,140
What? I'm not gonna marry you.

354
00:23:46,140 --> 00:23:52,820
Not that... I only request that you leave
without actually saying "goodbye."

355
00:23:52,820 --> 00:23:56,320
Oh, I've never said that to anyone, anyway.

356
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,020
I wanna see you again.

357
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:04,060
Alright, I'm off!

358
00:24:04,060 --> 00:24:05,060
See you!

359
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:06,630
Take care, Luffy!

360
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:08,900
See ya!

361
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:11,800
He said he wants to see me again!

362
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:13,200
Is this what they call...

363
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,310
a proposal?!

364
00:24:16,310 --> 00:24:19,080
Nyo, it's nyot!

365
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:22,550
Hey, you ran into me on purpose, didn't ya?

366
00:24:22,550 --> 00:24:25,750
Th-That guy is screwed!

367
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:28,680
Why don't you say something?

368
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:32,820
Did you run into me knowing who I was?

369
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:36,460
Use your eyes! You made me
look like a chump.

370
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:40,300
You humiliated me in public.

371
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,570
Me, of all people.

372
00:24:42,570 --> 00:24:46,240
I'm an elite pirate with a 400-million bounty!

373
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:49,440
Plant your knees on the grass, right now,

374
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,840
and beg for your life!

375
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:55,880
Just moments ago,

376
00:24:56,380 --> 00:25:02,180
a man with a long nose and a woman
with long hair crossed us,

377
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:05,520
so our captain is in a bad mood.

378
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:06,990
Apologize quickly.

379
00:25:07,690 --> 00:25:09,390
Prostrate yourself!

380
00:25:09,390 --> 00:25:14,900
Otherwise, this one little mistake
will end up costing your life.

381
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:18,230
Our captain has an itchy trigger finger.

382
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:23,570
Kneel on the ground already!
This guy is Straw Hat Luffy!

383
00:25:23,570 --> 00:25:26,410
Does he want to get killed? Apologize!

384
00:25:26,410 --> 00:25:28,540
I'm really sorry!

385
00:25:28,540 --> 00:25:30,650
I need to get going.

386
00:25:32,010 --> 00:25:34,450
– What's wrong with him?!
– What's wrong with him?!

387
00:25:35,890 --> 00:25:37,320
Okay!

388
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,820
That does it!

389
00:26:08,020 --> 00:26:11,520
Hey, did he do something just now?

390
00:26:51,790 --> 00:26:52,960
It's the Sunny!

391
00:27:00,540 --> 00:27:04,140
Sorry to keep you waiting for two years.

392
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,580
I'm glad you're okay!

393
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:16,750
We've got an absolute babe here!

394
00:27:16,750 --> 00:27:21,060
You're our super archaeologist...

395
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,800
Robin, aren't you?!

396
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:50,150
You haven't changed at all, Franky!

397
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:52,220
Of course I've changed, silly!

398
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:56,560
Witness the romantic masculinity
jam-packed in my body!

399
00:27:56,560 --> 00:28:01,760
Feast your eyes on this fantastic,
one-of-a-kind transformation!

400
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:08,040
I'm beyond human understanding now!

401
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:12,710
Yeah, you seem to have converted
much of your human side.

402
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:17,450
Hey, hey! You sayin' I'm perverted?

403
00:28:17,450 --> 00:28:18,680
What a great compliment!

404
00:28:27,660 --> 00:28:29,390
Is this the coating?

405
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:31,960
It's like jelly.

406
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:36,670
That's right! Rayleigh sure knows his stuff!

407
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:38,370
Now we can dive into the depths!

408
00:28:38,370 --> 00:28:41,400
It was masterfully done!

409
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:44,010
I just saw Rayleigh and the others.

410
00:28:44,010 --> 00:28:45,870
So you went to the bar.

411
00:28:45,870 --> 00:28:47,610
What number were you?

412
00:28:47,610 --> 00:28:48,910
Eighth.

413
00:28:49,510 --> 00:28:51,110
Everyone's here except Luffy.

414
00:28:51,550 --> 00:28:55,480
I see. We'll begin a new voyage soon.

415
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:57,820
I've got the ship in tip-top condition.

416
00:29:00,690 --> 00:29:03,460
The new weapons are ready, too!

417
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:06,630
I can't wait.

418
00:29:06,630 --> 00:29:08,730
By the way, where are the others?

419
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:11,900
Usopp and Sanji were here earlier.

420
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:14,170
Usopp left to buy fuel,

421
00:29:14,170 --> 00:29:16,640
and Sanji went shopping for food.

422
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:19,580
I see. Actually, on my way here...

423
00:29:20,980 --> 00:29:22,680
I found this.

424
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:27,720
Did you know about this? "Soul King," huh?

425
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:30,490
Yeah... About Brook...

426
00:29:30,490 --> 00:29:34,360
I knew about it. I've seen his TDs everywhere.

427
00:29:37,030 --> 00:29:39,630
He's in the spotlight now.

428
00:29:39,630 --> 00:29:42,800
From the dark, silent, foggy sea...

429
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:47,340
propelled into the bright lights of the stage,
cheered on by legions of fans.

430
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,710
He might not...

431
00:29:55,980 --> 00:30:02,950
want to be a pirate again.

432
00:30:02,950 --> 00:30:07,860
♪ Soul King is mysterious... ♪

433
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:11,590
♪ He's nothing but bones! ♪

434
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:21,670
♪ Afro on the skull! Girls love the contrast! ♪

435
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:21,670
♪ – Girls love the contrast! ♪
♪ – Girls love the contrast! ♪

436
00:30:21,670 --> 00:30:26,080
♪ Wanna make her weak in the knees? ♪

437
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:28,640
♪ Got milk! Got milk! ♪

438
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:36,620
♪ You need more calcium than protein! ♪

439
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,620
♪ – Ah-ahhh...! ♪
♪ – Ah-ahhh...! ♪

440
00:30:36,620 --> 00:30:38,020
Captain...!

441
00:30:38,020 --> 00:30:39,290
Captain Luffy!

442
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:41,890
Damn!

443
00:30:42,830 --> 00:30:44,330
Luffy!

444
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,800
I missed you guys!

445
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,000
Hey!

446
00:30:49,330 --> 00:30:50,200
Luffy!

447
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,200
What?

448
00:30:51,630 --> 00:30:52,800
Franky!

449
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:53,370
Huh?

450
00:30:53,770 --> 00:30:54,640
Nami!

451
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:55,470
Huh?!

452
00:30:58,240 --> 00:31:00,840
S... Sogeking?!

453
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,510
Hm?

454
00:31:01,510 --> 00:31:03,810
Cool!

455
00:31:04,150 --> 00:31:07,120
You guys have changed in the last two years!

456
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:09,390
I bet you got stronger!

457
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,650
It's the Straw Hats.

458
00:31:12,650 --> 00:31:15,290
What are they doing on the street?

459
00:31:15,290 --> 00:31:16,790
Well, what happened was...

460
00:31:16,790 --> 00:31:21,730
Avoid eye contact.
You don't want to fight them.

461
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:24,770
D-Dammit!

462
00:31:24,770 --> 00:31:26,970
What happened to you?

463
00:31:27,670 --> 00:31:28,870
I don't know!

464
00:31:29,670 --> 00:31:32,110
I felt chills all over my body!

465
00:31:34,110 --> 00:31:36,150
What kind of trick did he pull?

466
00:31:36,980 --> 00:31:40,650
Oh, yeah! We have another problem.

467
00:31:40,650 --> 00:31:42,150
The thing is, Cocoa got–

468
00:31:42,520 --> 00:31:43,620
No, I mean...

469
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:45,290
Nico Robin got...

470
00:31:45,290 --> 00:31:46,660
What was that, Zoro?!

471
00:31:46,660 --> 00:31:48,990
Nico Robin got abducted?!

472
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:52,490
I'm sorry. It happened right before our eyes.

473
00:31:52,490 --> 00:31:55,100
Yeah, that's right! This is serious, Luffy!

474
00:31:55,430 --> 00:31:58,630
She could have been kidnapped,
just like Camie was!

475
00:31:58,630 --> 00:31:59,940
Wha...?

476
00:32:01,070 --> 00:32:02,370
Who did it?

477
00:32:02,370 --> 00:32:05,570
Uh... I haven't the foggiest.

478
00:32:05,570 --> 00:32:06,710
Captain,

479
00:32:06,710 --> 00:32:12,410
I think the people who are after
the real Robin took Cocoa by mistake.

480
00:32:13,020 --> 00:32:14,320
That's possible.

481
00:32:15,220 --> 00:32:20,190
She looked so much like the real Robin...
That did not go in our favor.

482
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:22,620
Hey, stop whispering!

483
00:32:22,990 --> 00:32:24,190
What?

484
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:28,100
Well, not much we can do now.

485
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:29,830
That's her fate.

486
00:32:29,830 --> 00:32:30,470
– What?!
– What?!

487
00:32:30,470 --> 00:32:31,600
O-Okay, Captain.

488
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:32,470
What?!

489
00:32:32,470 --> 00:32:35,700
Hey, Luffy! Robin has been abducted!

490
00:32:36,870 --> 00:32:40,280
And what the hell is this creature?

491
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:43,650
Is that supposed to be a joke?!

492
00:32:43,650 --> 00:32:46,380
Now's not the time to say such things!

493
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:49,150
How can he speak? Is he a stuffed animal?

494
00:32:49,150 --> 00:32:50,750
Take it back, Luffy!

495
00:32:50,750 --> 00:32:51,950
Shut up!

496
00:32:56,060 --> 00:32:57,560
Forget about that thing!

497
00:32:57,560 --> 00:33:03,770
Just meet at Grove 46 with
the hundred recruits we found here!

498
00:33:04,170 --> 00:33:05,800
That long-nosed man...

499
00:33:06,270 --> 00:33:07,770
That orange-haired woman...

500
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:11,110
That brat with the cloak and giant backpack...

501
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:14,710
Find those three...

502
00:33:14,710 --> 00:33:19,520
and make them regret
crossing Straw Hat Luffy!

503
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,920
– Oh! Roger!
– Oh! Roger!

504
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:24,550
Let's do our best not to kill them
before bringing them here.

505
00:33:24,550 --> 00:33:28,760
Let's use this opportunity
to show them we mean business!

506
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,060
Okay, let's go!

507
00:33:30,060 --> 00:33:32,490
Wait a minute, you guys!

508
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:35,900
Have these last two years
warped your personalities so much?

509
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,300
Luffy?!

510
00:33:37,300 --> 00:33:41,000
I... I... feel so sad...

511
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:43,110
All I can do is cry!

512
00:33:43,670 --> 00:33:46,170
Again, what is this creature?

513
00:33:46,170 --> 00:33:49,980
What about Robin? Why don't
you guys say something?!

514
00:33:49,980 --> 00:33:52,750
Huh? How can he talk?

515
00:33:52,750 --> 00:33:55,250
Toys today are pretty advanced!

516
00:33:55,250 --> 00:33:59,290
Dammit! You guys aren't
at all who I thought you were!

517
00:33:59,290 --> 00:34:03,130
I'll go save her all on my own!

518
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:10,630
Wait for me, Robin!

519
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:14,240
What happened?

520
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:15,770
Is there some infighting?

521
00:34:16,410 --> 00:34:17,370
It's them...

522
00:34:18,210 --> 00:34:20,080
No doubt about it.

523
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:24,610
The Straw Hat Pirates may look
radically different from two years ago,

524
00:34:25,710 --> 00:34:28,220
but no one else has a weird pet like that!

525
00:34:28,780 --> 00:34:29,950
They're...

526
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,790
the Straw Hats!

527
00:34:32,790 --> 00:34:34,420
They're alive!

528
00:34:38,260 --> 00:34:43,230
Hey, fisherman! Any deals on today's catch?

529
00:34:43,230 --> 00:34:44,900
Huh? Are they out?

530
00:34:47,340 --> 00:34:49,240
Hey, are you the owner?

531
00:34:51,340 --> 00:34:52,340
What's the matter?

532
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:54,510
He's gone!

533
00:34:54,510 --> 00:34:56,280
The green-haired man that was here!

534
00:34:56,850 --> 00:34:57,810
Green-haired...?

535
00:34:58,210 --> 00:34:59,720
What happened?

536
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:01,650
I did something horrible!

537
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:04,750
It was just a few moments ago...

538
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:07,690
Old man, I'd like to go fishing.

539
00:35:05,690 --> 00:35:06,490
Huh?

540
00:35:07,690 --> 00:35:08,660
Wha...?

541
00:35:09,590 --> 00:35:13,400
Young man, you don't
look like the fishing type.

542
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:16,830
I promised to meet friends on this island,

543
00:35:16,830 --> 00:35:20,840
but I got here first and
haven't seen any of them yet.

544
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:24,010
Being first has left me with nothing to do.

545
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:26,580
Can you take me out
on your fishing boat?

546
00:35:26,580 --> 00:35:30,780
Sure, I'll take you out on that boat,
so why don't you wait for me on board?

547
00:35:32,710 --> 00:35:35,080
That's what I told him.

548
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:38,790
Green hair, three swords, and a bellyband?

549
00:35:38,790 --> 00:35:42,360
Yeah, and he has a deep scar on his eye.

550
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,060
You know him?

551
00:35:43,060 --> 00:35:44,760
A scar on his eye?

552
00:35:45,460 --> 00:35:47,030
Was it this guy?

553
00:35:47,030 --> 00:35:50,900
Oh yeah, this is the guy! Is he your friend?

554
00:35:50,900 --> 00:35:53,400
I'd say more of an acquaintance...

555
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:58,470
So I told him to get on
the fishing boat, yes I did.

556
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:01,440
But when I got back here...

557
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:04,850
Young man! Wrong one!

558
00:36:04,850 --> 00:36:07,620
You boarded a pirate ship!

559
00:36:07,620 --> 00:36:12,390
Alright, men! Time to fulfill our dreams
and set sail for the New World!

560
00:36:13,660 --> 00:36:16,120
W-Wake up, young man!

561
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:18,630
You're on the wrong ship!

562
00:36:18,630 --> 00:36:23,900
So I think he's heading
for Fishman Island like that.

563
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:30,340
That idiot!

564
00:36:35,340 --> 00:36:37,910
I thought it was unlike him to show up first.

565
00:36:37,910 --> 00:36:42,220
But sure enough, he ended up
doing something like this...!

566
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:45,220
He was on a pirate ship!
He might be dead by now!

567
00:36:45,220 --> 00:36:49,190
No, no, it's okay. It's not your fault at all.

568
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:53,730
He won't die. We're just lucky
we know where he's heading.

569
00:36:53,730 --> 00:36:55,200
That aside, can I have some fish?

570
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:57,200
Sure, but...

571
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:58,600
Hey, what's that?!

572
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:02,670
Look at the water! Something is surfacing!

573
00:37:04,970 --> 00:37:05,910
What is it?

574
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:08,340
It's huge!

575
00:37:20,020 --> 00:37:21,890
It's a galleon!

576
00:37:21,890 --> 00:37:25,090
Was it poorly coated
and crushed by the water pressure?

577
00:37:25,090 --> 00:37:26,800
Or attacked by sea kings?

578
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:30,470
It looks like it's been cut clean in half!

579
00:37:30,470 --> 00:37:31,630
Don't be crazy!

580
00:37:31,630 --> 00:37:34,140
What could cut a ship this big?

581
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:35,600
You bastard!

582
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:39,510
How dare you ruin our dream
of going to the New World?!

583
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,380
A twist of fate!

584
00:37:43,380 --> 00:37:45,610
You should blame your own cursed fate that

585
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:48,550
brought a plague onto your ship.

586
00:37:48,550 --> 00:37:50,550
So self-righteous!

587
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:51,520
Look!

588
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:52,790
Somebody's on the ship!

589
00:37:52,790 --> 00:37:57,230
Oh, he's back. Could've stayed
gone for all I care.

590
00:38:05,870 --> 00:38:07,100
I got on...

591
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:09,840
the wrong ship.

592
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:21,250
Ten-Odd Days Later at a Bar

593
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:21,250
Ten-Odd Days Later at a Bar

